  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are currently net buying with SPX at 7026.62, positioned between the max negative gamma at 7015 (-2419.1M) and the massive positive gamma wall at 7050 (+10690.9M). The recent wall break event combined with the -4.4% 1-min drop suggests aggressive selling pressure, but dealers' long gamma position means they're providing liquidity by buying this dip and will aggressively sell any bounce toward 7050. Watch for strong resistance at the 7050 level where dealers hold over 10.6B in positive gamma, and support around 7015 where negative gamma forces them to buy.\n\nThe thick positive gamma walls stacked at 7000, 7030, 7035, 7050, and 7100 create a stabilizing regime that should limit large directional moves and promote mean reversion within this range.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to stabilize and chop between 7015-7050 with dealers capping upside moves.",
